films.title: Star Wars: A New Hope
films.notes: The textbook monomyth; Lucas explicitly modelled on Campbell

films.title: The Matrix
films.notes: Dense monomyth with Gnostic and Buddhist layers; Neo as messiah-hero

films.title: The Lion King
films.notes: Hamlet via Campbell; atonement with father is core structural element

films.title: Arrival
films.notes: Inverted monomyth; the 'return' precedes the departure structurally

films.title: No Country for Old Men
films.notes: Anti-hero's journey; deliberate Campbell inversion â€” hero fails, shadow wins

films.title: Whiplash
films.notes: Compressed internal journey; mentor-as-shadow subverts archetype; no supernatural elements

films.title: The Wizard of Oz
films.notes: Pure departure-return arc; return home as ultimate boon; strong herald/trickster elements

films.title: Mad Max: Fury Road
films.notes: Dual protagonist; Furiosa carries the true monomyth; return with elixir (the wives, the green place)

films.title: Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind
films.notes: Inverted internal journey; the special world is memory/mind; no external quest

films.title: Spirited Away
films.notes: Child hero; spirit world as special world; return with elixir = personal growth & parents saved
